name (Nathan Hale Sr 1784-1863) and reached into her children's generation through her son's cousin marriage to her sister Sybella Hale Hall's daughter Sarah."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Died of dementia paralytica at Northampton, 1867","body":"Died December 21, 1867 at Northampton MA age 79 — eighteen months after her husband — with cause given on her death record as 'Dementile Paralysis,' the period name for dementia paralytica, the late-stage neurological syndrome of progressive cognitive and motor decline."}],"slug":"octavia-hale-1788"},"H00529":{"id":"H00529","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1766,"month":11,"day":26,"city":"Northampton","state":"Massachusetts","county":"Hampshire","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1861,"month":2,"day":27,"city":"Westhampton","county":"Hampshire","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00264","mother_id":"I00043"},"tags":["extraordinary_longevity","physician"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 529"}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":2,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I01155","date_year":1788,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1810,"children_ids":["H01409","H01410","H01411","H01412","H01413","H01414","H01415"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"I01156","date_year":1812,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1847,"children_ids":[]}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Dr. William Hooker","first_name":"William","last_name":"Hooker","title":"Dr.","married_names":[]},"residence":{"city":"Westhampton","county":"Hampshire","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"is_placeholder":false,"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM544"},"education":[],"career":[{"role":"Physician","location":"Westhampton, Hampshire County, Massachusetts","notes":"Practiced medicine at Westhampton MA per EH 1909 #529. Established the Hooker physician tradition in Westhampton continued by son Dr. Anson Hooker (H01414, 1799-1869) and through several Westhampton descendants."},{"role":"Trader / Merchant","location":"Westhampton, Hampshire County, Massachusetts","notes":"Per EH 1909 #529: 'He was a physician and also a trader at West Hampton, Mass.' — supplementing physician income with a trading operation, common pattern for rural New England doctors of the period."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Lived to ninety-four as Westhampton physician","body":"Born Northampton MA 1766; died Westhampton MA February 27, 1861 at age ninety-four — extraordinary longevity spanning the early Republic through the Civil War's outbreak. Practiced medicine in Westhampton MA and also operated as a trader; both occupations supported a large family of seven children with first wife Anna Thompson before her 1810 death."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Lost wife at forty-two, remarried after two years","body":"First wife Anna Thompson died Westhampton April 2, 1810 at age forty-two — leaving him with seven children ranging from twenty-four-year-old Henry down to eight-year-old Edward. William remarried 1812 to Rhoda Phelps, widow of Ensign Hartland of Hartland Connecticut. No documented children from the second marriage; Rhoda predeceased William by fourteen years."}],"former_ids":[],"slug":"william-hooker-1766"},"I01155":{"id":"I01155","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Anna","last_name":"Hooker","mai