r","body":"Elder brother of Capt Nathan Hale (1755-1776) — the Continental Army officer hanged by the British at New York September 22, 1776 with the final words 'I only regret that I have but one life to lose for my country.' Enoch survived him by 61 years and shaped his own son's name around the family memory."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"First minister of West Hampton Massachusetts","body":"Settled at West Hampton MA as the new parish's first minister, where he served the gathered congregation through his long life. Daughter Octavia (1788-1867) born at Westhampton would marry William Hooker Jr there December 19, 1811 and carry the Hale-Hooker connection into the Westfield and Hartford banking families."}],"slug":"enoch-hale-1753"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}